# TAIL ITEM 1 — abstract-type REPRESENTATION bound `<= REP`.
#
# Corpus pattern (recon-confirmed, e.g. srcgen2/SATS/xstamp0.sats):
#   abstype stamp_type <= uint
# declares an OPAQUE abstract type WITH a representation witness (`stamp` is rep'd as `uint`).
# The `<= REP` is CODEGEN-ONLY / informational at typecheck: stock f0_abstype carries it ONLY in
# the D2Cabstype node's second field (A2TDFlteq), never installing a subtype relation on the
# s2cst; trans23/trans2a pass the a2tdf through as `_` and never inspect it (investigation-proven).
#
# Our `@abstract type NAME <= REP` now parses the optional `<= REP`, threads it through PyAST ->
# PyCore -> build_abstype, and lowers to D2Cabstype(s2cst, A2TDFlteq(<lowered REP>)). Opacity at
# typecheck is UNCHANGED (the abstract singleton typechecks identically with or without the rep),
# so this fixture must reach nerror=0.
#
# This fixture: an abstract type `Stamp` with a representation bound `<= Int`, an `@extern` foreign
# constructor producing a `Stamp`, and a use that typechecks against the opaque `Stamp` type.

@abstract type Stamp <= Int

@extern
def stamp_make(x: Int) -> Stamp

def use_stamp(n: Int) -> Stamp:
    stamp_make(n)
